1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,040
Let's get started. The title of our analysis today is Super Mario:

2
00:00:05,040 --> 00:00:10,880
AI Sabotages Us, and I assure you we will explore a truly fascinating scientific study

3
00:00:10,880 --> 00:00:14,599
and, frankly, a completely counter-intuitive one.

4
00:00:14,599 --> 00:00:17,760
We are putting under the magnifying glass academic research

5
00:00:17,760 --> 00:00:21,800
that will literally tear apart many of the beliefs we take for granted

6
00:00:21,800 --> 00:00:25,839
about artificial intelligence, automation, and teamwork.

7
00:00:25,839 --> 00:00:29,120
Fasten your seatbelts, because it's going to be quite a journey.

8
00:00:29,160 --> 00:00:31,160
Let's imagine this scene for a moment.

9
00:00:31,160 --> 00:00:33,640
We have a tight-knit team that works very well.

10
00:00:33,640 --> 00:00:38,000
At some point, the company decides to replace one of the flesh-and-blood colleagues

11
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:41,120
with a perfect artificial intelligence.

12
00:00:41,120 --> 00:00:44,760
A machine that never gets distracted, performs tasks at lightning speed,

13
00:00:44,760 --> 00:00:46,600
and without a single error.

14
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:49,040
Conventional logic would lead us to think

15
00:00:49,040 --> 00:00:51,960
that productivity should skyrocket, right?

16
00:00:51,960 --> 00:00:57,600
I mean, it seems like the perfect move, yet reality slams a resounding paradox in our faces.

17
00:00:57,840 --> 00:01:00,679
Chapter 1: The AI Paradox.

18
00:01:00,679 --> 00:01:05,400
To understand what's happening, let's take a look at an amazing laboratory experiment

19
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:08,640
conducted by researchers Dell'Acqua, Kogut, and Perkowski.

20
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:12,280
They wanted to measure not just the cold results of automation,

21
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:15,280
but the real impact on the behavior of human colleagues.

22
00:01:15,280 --> 00:01:17,760
And there is one starting point that is unequivocal.

23
00:01:17,760 --> 00:01:21,079
Taken individually, AI is objectively superior.

24
00:01:21,079 --> 00:01:24,920
Working alone, it manages to retrieve an average of 7.5 ingredients,

25
00:01:24,920 --> 00:01:28,120
while the human stops at an average of 6.4.

26
00:01:28,120 --> 00:01:30,480
The algorithm totally dominates.

27
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:34,200
In short, on paper, it is literally the ideal candidate.

28
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:37,799
Chapter 2: The Super Mario Experiment.

29
00:01:37,799 --> 00:01:42,640
But how do you test the impact of this perfect employee in the field?

30
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:45,359
The researchers had a brilliant intuition:

31
00:01:45,359 --> 00:01:48,760
use a famous video game, Super Mario Party,

32
00:01:48,760 --> 00:01:54,200
transforming it into a real microcosm to simulate company dynamics.

33
00:01:54,320 --> 00:01:58,000
They created human teams whose task was to move in sync

34
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:00,520
to collect ingredients against the clock.

35
00:02:00,520 --> 00:02:02,200
The groups started playing,

36
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:04,680
creating their routines naturally.

37
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:06,600
Then, the teams were split up;

38
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:08,439
some remained unchanged,

39
00:02:08,439 --> 00:02:10,680
others welcomed a new human player,

40
00:02:10,680 --> 00:02:13,439
and others, well, were given automation.

41
00:02:13,439 --> 00:02:16,039
And here's the real twist.

42
00:02:16,039 --> 00:02:20,599
Mid-game, after 6 rounds in which the human teams had gotten into the rhythm

43
00:02:20,599 --> 00:02:23,599
and understood each other almost instantly, everything changes.

44
00:02:23,639 --> 00:02:25,879
Suddenly, and without warning,

45
00:02:25,879 --> 00:02:29,000
a flesh-and-blood player is removed from the team

46
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:33,199
and replaced by that super-performing artificial intelligence,

47
00:02:33,199 --> 00:02:35,560
set to the maximum difficulty level,

48
00:02:35,560 --> 00:02:38,400
capable of calculating paths with millimeter precision

49
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:40,240
in a fraction of a second.

50
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:41,240
The result?

51
00:02:41,240 --> 00:02:43,159
Absolutely shocking.

52
00:02:43,159 --> 00:02:45,439
We would have expected an efficiency boom,

53
00:02:45,439 --> 00:02:48,120
but instead, the teams assigned the AI

54
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:50,079
literally collapsed.

55
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:55,440
Overall, they brought back 6.12 fewer ingredients than the control groups.

56
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:59,080
And mind you, we're not just talking about little numbers in a game.

57
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:05,880
This collapse cost participants a real 13% loss on their financial bonus at the end of the experiment.

58
00:03:05,880 --> 00:03:08,920
And here we come to the heart of the matter,

59
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:11,439
the real mystery of this investigation:

60
00:03:11,439 --> 00:03:16,760
if artificial intelligence is so immensely capable and fast on its own,

61
00:03:16,760 --> 00:03:19,160
why does it drag the whole team down?

62
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:21,560
What broke in the mechanism?

63
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:22,759
Chapter 3: The Coordination Collapse.

64
00:03:22,759 --> 00:03:25,199
The first big suspect is a real physical short circuit in teamwork.

65
00:03:25,199 --> 00:03:30,919
The arrival of the machine destroyed the group's routines.

66
00:03:30,919 --> 00:03:34,319
We humans develop implicit habits.

67
00:03:34,319 --> 00:03:37,199
We coordinate to avoid getting in each other's way, right?

68
00:03:37,199 --> 00:03:40,519
The AI doesn't.

69
00:03:40,519 --> 00:03:41,319
The result?

70
00:03:41,319 --> 00:03:42,439
Human and AI characters literally ended up constantly bumping into each other.

71
00:03:42,439 --> 00:03:48,039
Consider that while the addition of a new human colleague increased collisions

72
00:03:48,199 --> 00:03:52,439
by a mere 0.48,

73
00:03:52,439 --> 00:03:54,840
the introduction of the AI caused almost three more collisions per round.

74
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:58,799
The AI followed technically impeccable paths, yes,

75
00:03:58,799 --> 00:04:01,840
but ones totally unpredictable to the human mind, sowing chaos.

76
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:06,039
Chapter 4: Human Trust and Motivation.

77
00:04:06,039 --> 00:04:07,399
But these physical collisions are only one piece of the puzzle.

78
00:04:07,399 --> 00:04:09,719
To truly understand the collapse in productivity,

79
00:04:09,719 --> 00:04:13,519
we must dig into the psychological impact on the remaining human workers.

80
00:04:13,519 --> 00:04:16,279
The end-of-game surveys are clear and quite alarming.

81
00:04:16,320 --> 00:04:20,640
It's not that people felt a deep hatred for technology;

82
00:04:20,640 --> 00:04:25,040
algorithmic aversion, in fact, remained virtually unchanged.

83
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:28,840
The real disaster was something else.

84
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:33,240
There was a drastic drop in trust within the team,

85
00:04:33,240 --> 00:04:35,560
and as a result, people simply reduced their effort—

86
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:38,640
they threw in the towel.

87
00:04:38,640 --> 00:04:42,520
The key point to take home is that human effort

88
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:44,480
is not an "always on" switch;

89
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:47,600
it's deeply conditioned by the surrounding environment.

90
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:49,720
The data tells us that a full 84% of participants

91
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:53,160
by far preferred working with other humans.

92
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:57,040
When the AI swept away that crucial component

93
00:04:57,040 --> 00:05:00,240
of interaction and sociality from the workplace,

94
00:05:00,240 --> 00:05:03,360
people's motivation plummeted,

95
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:06,000
erasing in one fell swoop every benefit brought by the algorithm.

96
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:08,600
Chapter 5: The Skill Difference.

97
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:12,680
At this point, however, a critical variable comes into play:

98
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:14,120
the one that determined which teams imploded

99
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:16,600
and which survived the machine's integration:

100
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:19,879
the level of baseline skills.

101
00:05:19,879 --> 00:05:22,480
The numbers speak clearly.

102
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:25,399
For teams with low or medium skills,

103
00:05:25,399 --> 00:05:27,480
the impact was devastating—a massive collapse.

104
00:05:27,480 --> 00:05:28,879
But for highly competent teams, the story changes,

105
00:05:28,879 --> 00:05:30,800
showing even a slight improvement.

106
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:33,879
Why?

107
00:05:33,879 --> 00:05:36,800
Because only groups that already had solid foundations

108
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:39,120
had the flexibility to absorb the shock

109
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:39,879
and adapt to the AI's frantic pace.

110
00:05:39,879 --> 00:05:43,000
Chapter 6: The Future of Work.

111
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:45,319
And here we are at the point.

112
00:05:45,319 --> 00:05:47,720
If we take all this and transfer it from the video game

113
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:49,160
to real offices,

114
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:51,319
we finally understand the current AI productivity paradox,

115
00:05:51,319 --> 00:05:53,000
where massive technological investments

116
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:04,120
almost never correspond to an immediate return.

117
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:07,399
Simply dropping an AI from above into a work environment

118
00:06:07,399 --> 00:06:10,800
usually fails for three essential reasons.

119
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:13,600
First, the machine shatters existing routines.

120
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:16,840
Second, by removing the human component,

121
00:06:16,840 --> 00:06:19,319
social motivation withers.

122
00:06:19,319 --> 00:06:21,800
And third, to compensate for all this,

123
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:24,199
workers need very high-level skills

124
00:06:24,199 --> 00:06:27,400
that, frankly, are not that widespread.

125
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:29,800
This concept is perfectly summarized

126
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:32,319
in a quote by the study's authors who say:

127
00:06:32,319 --> 00:06:35,360
"Successful AI introduction

128
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:37,519
will require augmenting humans through AI

129
00:06:37,519 --> 00:06:40,519
rather than potentially demoralizing them."

130
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:43,319
And right here is the heart of the matter.

131
00:06:43,319 --> 00:06:47,799
The real challenge organizations face

132
00:06:47,799 --> 00:06:50,759
is not purely technological; it's socio-technical.

133
00:06:50,759 --> 00:06:53,359
We must learn to exploit the power of algorithms

134
00:06:53,359 --> 00:06:55,959
while ensuring that people maintain

135
00:06:55,959 --> 00:06:57,719
trust and motivation.

136
00:06:57,719 --> 00:07:00,759
And all this leaves us with one final question,

137
00:07:00,759 --> 00:07:03,399
provocative and decidedly tough:

138
00:07:03,399 --> 00:07:06,399
Are we investing billions to design an artificial intelligence

139
00:07:06,399 --> 00:07:09,560
that aims only at the cold replacement of workers,

140
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:12,280
or are we really trying to create work environments

141
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:15,839
where humans and algorithms can thrive together in harmony?

142
00:07:15,839 --> 00:07:18,319
It's a nuance that will make all the difference in the world

143
00:07:18,319 --> 00:07:21,439
between an extraordinary success and an organizational failure.

144
00:07:21,439 --> 00:07:25,040
The hybrid future is full of pitfalls.

145
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:27,240
We hope this analysis has left you wanting

146
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:29,800
to delve even deeper into this crucial topic.

147
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:29,800
Until next time.